{"id": "1483393467311722657", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "author_id": "259018461458595850", "author_name": "amstelredam", "content": "大姐 means “Big Sis” in a family way, AND when calling a female person who is kind of respected (such as “boss” but not as formal as “boss”), AND when calling whoever is kind of stupid (and 90% situation when they are a female). So if that specific 大姐 is Kath’a fellow calling her in a way close to “boss”, then it can be “Kath” in English 🙂", "timestamp": "2026-03-17T09:16:02.725000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["223291046250020865"], "reactions": [{"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "reply_to": "1483183466861297684"}
