{"id": "1483532445109325947", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "author_id": "407535113312927745", "author_name": "shaw_51", "content": "Kathigura is the leader of the gang. Calling her ‘Big Sis’ emphasizes the tough gang-sister vibe much more, whereas simply using ‘Kath’ highlights the family-like bond between them. So in this context, I personally think ‘Big Sis’ is the better translation for ‘大姐’, but yeah, both work.", "timestamp": "2026-03-17T18:28:17.614000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["223291046250020865"], "reactions": [{"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "reply_to": "1483183466861297684"}
{"id": "1483552683792011455", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "author_id": "259018461458595850", "author_name": "amstelredam", "content": "True, I think the reason why sometimes “Kath” works is because “Big Sis” is not as orally common as 大姐 is in Chinese…", "timestamp": "2026-03-17T19:48:42.892000+00:00", "reactions": [{"emoji": "👍", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}]}
